13/10/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Foreign Minister Skender Hyseni announced on Saturday (October 11th) that Kosovo recognises Macedonia under its constitutional name. 
"Macedonia's name is not up for discussion. 
Kosovo recognises Macedonia under the name that its government and citizens prefer," Hyseni told the BBC.
In other news Saturday, government spokesperson Memli Krasniqi said the cabinet is preparing to defend the legality of Kosovo's declaration of independence from Serbia before the International Court of Justice. 
Kosovo will gather the best local and international experts to defend its case before the court, Krasniqi added. 
(Koha Ditore, Zeri - 13/10/08; Kohavision, RTK, Koha Ditore, Express, Kosova Sot - 12/10/08; BBC - 11/10/08)
